# Fix spinner freeze during `sentry cli upgrade`

## Problem

The spinner next to "Downloading" freezes intermittently because
`applyPatch()` in `src/lib/bspatch.ts:345-349` blocks the event loop
with a byte-by-byte diff loop processing millions of bytes. The spinner
runs via `setTimeout` at 50ms intervals (`src/lib/polling.ts:141`), so
any synchronous work exceeding ~40ms causes a visible stutter.

## Changes

### 1. Periodic yielding in `applyPatch()` — `src/lib/bspatch.ts`

Add amortized time-check yielding inside the inner diff byte loop
(lines 345-349). `applyPatch()` is already `async`, so no signature
changes are needed anywhere in the call chain.

Add constants and a `lastYield` timestamp before the outer control loop,
then check inside the inner loop:

```typescript
const FRAME_BUDGET_MS = 40; // 25fps, under spinner's 50ms interval
const CHECK_MASK = 0xFFF;   // check clock every 4096 bytes

// ... existing setup ...

let lastYield = performance.now();

try {
  for (/* existing control loop */) {
    // ... existing parsing ...

    if (readDiffBy > 0) {
      const diffChunk = await diffReader.read(readDiffBy);
      const outputChunk = new Uint8Array(readDiffBy);

      for (let i = 0; i < readDiffBy; i++) {
        outputChunk[i] =
          ((oldFile[oldpos + i] ?? 0) + (diffChunk[i] ?? 0)) % 256;

        // Yield periodically so the spinner can animate
        if ((i & CHECK_MASK) === 0 && i > 0) {
          const now = performance.now();
          if (now - lastYield >= FRAME_BUDGET_MS) {
            await Bun.sleep(0);
            lastYield = performance.now();
          }
        }
      }

      // ... rest unchanged ...
    }

    // ... extra chunk + seek unchanged ...
  }
}
```

### 2. AsyncLocalStorage progress context — `src/lib/polling.ts`

Add an `AsyncLocalStorage`-based progress context so any function in the
async call chain can update the spinner message without parameter threading.

At the top of the file, add:

```typescript
import { AsyncLocalStorage } from "node:async_hooks";

const progressStorage = new AsyncLocalStorage<(msg: string) => void>();

/**
 * Update the active spinner message from anywhere in the async call chain.
 * No-op if no spinner is active (no store, JSON mode, non-TTY).
 */
export function setProgressMessage(msg: string): void {
  progressStorage.getStore()?.(msg);
}
```

In `withProgress()`, wrap the callback invocation in `progressStorage.run()`:

```typescript
// Current (line 212):
return await fn(spinner.setMessage);

// Change to:
return await progressStorage.run(spinner.setMessage, () =>
  fn(spinner.setMessage)
);
```

The no-op branch (JSON/plain mode, line 202-206) also needs wrapping to
keep the store consistent — wrap with a no-op function or skip (either
works since `getStore()` returning `undefined` is already handled).

### 3. Progress message in patch loop — `src/lib/delta-upgrade.ts`

In `applyPatchesSequentially()` (line 1130), add a single line inside
the `for` loop to update the spinner:

```typescript
import { setProgressMessage } from "./polling.js";

// Inside the for loop, before the withTracing call:
setProgressMessage(
  `Applying patch ${i + 1}/${chain.patches.length}...`
);
```

No signature changes to any function in the call chain.

